analysis: The documents in this cluster primarily concern the establishment, modification, and authorization of military and civilian awards, medals, ribbons, and insignia. They cover a range of conflicts and services, from World War II to Vietnam, Afghanistan, and Iraq, as well as service within the White House and contributions to the American Revolution Bicentennial. The documents also include the establishment of official symbols, such as the Seal of the CIA, the Flag of the Navy, and the Coats of Arms for the President and Vice President.
title: Recognition and Commendation
